h6. Steps to reproduce
# Go to GIT Repo and try;
{noformat}
mkdir áa
cd áa
touch a.test
git add áa
{noformat}
# Commit the file a.test from source tree and it fails with:
{noformat}
git add a\314\201a/b.text 
fatal: pathspec 'a\314\201a/b.text' did not match any files
Completed with errors, see above
{noformat}

https://support.atlassian.com/browse/STSP-25
{quote}
Both git and mercurial support paths starting with tilde in their ignore files. SourceTree should use this style when setting the ignore configs so that way the config file is portable across multiple systems. For example, in my case I synchronize my ~/.gitconfig across all my machines, but they have different $HOME values, so I need to use the tilde format.
{quote}
